FBIS4-16457 "drsov074_b_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Rocket, Artillery Academy Recreated Rocket, Artillery Academy Recreated LD1704114994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 17 Apr 94 LD1704114994 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey Kokoshin announced the recreation of the Russian Academy of Rocket and Artillery Sciences during a visit to the St. Petersburg Artillery Museum on Saturday. He said that a decree on this was signed by Russian President Boris Yeltsin on 5 April. Sixty-nine research institutes and military-industrial firms have become founders of the academy. Professor Vladimir Keyeyev, doctor of technical sciences, has been elected president of the academy. The Russian Information Agency recalls that the artillery academy was originally set up in 1946 and closed down in 1953.
